g(x)\in \Bbb R
x\in \Bbb R
g^2(x)-g(x+1)-\dfrac{x^2+2x-6}{4}=0,   g(0)=0
g(x)
x\longrightarrow x+1
g^2(x+1)-g(x+2)-\dfrac{(x+1)^2+2(x+1)-6}{4}=0
g^2(x+2)-g(x+3)-\dfrac{(x+2)^2+2(x+2)-6}{4}=0
\cdots\cdots 
g^2(x+n)-g(x+n+1)-\dfrac{(x+n)^2+2(x+n)-6}{4}=0
\,x=-1\;
g(-1)^2-g(0)-\frac{(-1)^2+2(-1)-6}4=0\implies g(-1)^2=-\frac74
g(x)=\sum_{n\ge i\ge 0} a_ix^i
\displaystyle \frac{x^2+2x-6}4= g^2(x)-g(x+1)=(\sum_{n\ge i\ge 0} a_ix^i)^2-\sum_{n\ge i\ge 0} a_i(x+1)^i=a^2_nx^{2n}+\cdots
x
n=1
a_1=\frac12
\implies g(x)=\frac x2+a_0
g(0)=0
g(0)=a_0\implies \displaystyle  a_0=0\implies g(x)=\frac x2
\displaystyle g^2(x)-g(x+1)=\left(\frac x2\right)^2-\frac{x+1}2=\frac{x^2-2x-2}4
\displaystyle\frac{x^2+2x-6}4
